---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const stages = [
  {
    color: 'green',
    num: '1',
    stage: 'Stage 1',
    timeframe: 'Day 0&ndash;21',
    body: 'The earliest days. We weigh every puppy every day to make sure each one is thriving, and we give every puppy gentle, individual handling each day. Research shows that early, consistent handling is the meaningful ingredient in these first weeks &mdash; so that&rsquo;s exactly where we put our attention.'
  },
  {
    color: 'blue',
    num: '2',
    stage: 'Stage 2',
    timeframe: 'Week 3&ndash;6',
    body: 'The socialization period opens. Puppies&rsquo; eyes and ears are working, they&rsquo;re beginning to explore, and they start meeting the world at their own pace &mdash; novel objects, varied surfaces, new sounds, gentle new experiences.'
  },
  {
    color: 'yellow',
    num: '3',
    stage: 'Stage 3',
    timeframe: 'Week 6&ndash;Go-Home',
    body: 'The heart of early socialization. Puppies begin leaving the property to meet people, see new places, and encounter friendly, healthy adult dogs.'
  },
  {
    color: 'red',
    num: '4',
    stage: 'Stage 4',
    timeframe: 'Go-Home&ndash;12 Months',
    body: 'Your stage. This is where you carry the momentum forward, and it contains the single most important window of all &mdash; one that closes around 12 to 14 weeks, just a few weeks after your puppy comes home. We give every family clear guidance for making the most of it.'
  }
];

const included = [
  {
    title: 'PuppyQ Certification',
    body: 'Proof your puppy met the full socialization standard.'
  },
  {
    title: 'PuppyQ Scorecard',
    body: 'Your puppy&rsquo;s seven-week snapshot, and later the eight-month follow-up.'
  },
  {
    title: 'PuppyQ History',
    body: 'The complete record of everything your puppy experienced along the way: the people, the places, and the milestones that shaped their start in life.'
  }
];
---
<Layout title="Our Program" description="The PuppyQ Framework &mdash; an evidence-based approach to raising healthy, calm, well-socialized Australian Labradoodle puppies.">

  <!-- HERO / INTRO -->
  <div class="page-hero pq-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Our Program</p>
      <h1>The PuppyQ Framework</h1>
      <p class="pq-hero-body">PuppyQ is an evidence-based framework for raising healthy and successful puppies. Adams Farm raises each puppy following PuppyQ protocols and provides a PuppyQ Scorecard and History.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- EVIDENCE-BASED EARLY SOCIALIZATION -->
  <section class="section pq-sec-white">
    <div class="container pq-narrow">
      <h2>Evidence-based early socialization</h2>
      <p>PuppyQ Protocols follows the guidelines of the American Veterinary Society of Animal Behavior (AVSAB), which is supported and endorsed by the American Veterinary Medical Association (AVMA). The AVSAB writes:</p>
      <blockquote class="pq-quote">&ldquo;The primary and most important time for puppy socialization is the first three months of life. During this time puppies should be exposed to as many new people, animals, stimuli and environments as can be achieved safely and without causing overstimulation.&rdquo;</blockquote>
      <a href="https://avsab.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Puppy_Socialization_Position_Statement_Download_-_10-3-14.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="pq-link">Read the full AVSAB position statement &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT "Q" MEANS -->
  <section class="section pq-sec-dark">
    <div class="container pq-narrow">
      <h2>PuppyQ &ndash; Q is for Quotient</h2>
      <p>Q stands for Quotient. We track thirteen of them, using C-BARQ &mdash; a validated behavior assessment from the University of Pennsylvania. It measures things like trainability, energy, and how your puppy responds to new people, dogs, and situations.</p>
      <p>C-BARQ &mdash; the Canine Behavioral Assessment and Research Questionnaire &mdash; was developed at the University of Pennsylvania by Dr. James Serpell and Dr. Yuying Hsu in 2003, to give owners and researchers a standardized way to measure real canine behavior. It&rsquo;s since been used in tens of thousands of evaluations worldwide. PuppyQ provides this evaluation to all forever families to help measure and improve its protocols.</p>
      <p>In conjunction with C-BARQ, PuppyQ has also developed its own Q Assessment, given to puppies at seven weeks by our certified ambassadors, before the puppy goes to its forever home. The Q Assessment is not used as a predictor of behavior, but as a look at the puppy&rsquo;s early traits and temperament.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SOCIALIZATION GOAL -->
  <section class="section pq-sec-cream">
    <div class="container pq-narrow">
      <h2>PuppyQ Socialization Benchmarks</h2>
      <p>Dr. Ian Dunbar is a veterinarian and animal behaviorist who holds a veterinary degree from the Royal Veterinary College in London and a doctorate in animal behavior from UC Berkeley. In 1982, he founded SIRIUS&reg; Puppy Training, the world&rsquo;s first off-leash puppy socialization program, and went on to found the Association of Professional Dog Trainers, now the largest dog trainer organization in the world. His socialization benchmark is one of the most widely cited in the field &mdash; not because it&rsquo;s official policy from any single body, but because decades of trainers, behaviorists, and veterinarians have converged on it independently.</p>
      <p>Our socialization goal follows his two-part benchmark: 100 people by 8 weeks with us, and 100 more in the first month home with you. It&rsquo;s a shared effort &mdash; we lay the foundation during your puppy&rsquo;s first weeks, and you carry it forward through the most formative days of their life.</p>
      <p>To earn PuppyQ Certification, each puppy meets a clear standard by 8 weeks: 10 events, 10 locations, and 100 people. It&rsquo;s a floor we hold ourselves to for every single puppy.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FOUR STAGES -->
  <section class="section s-pq-stages">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Four stages, birth to one year</h2>
      <p class="s-pq-stages-intro">PuppyQ organizes a puppy&rsquo;s first year into four developmental stages. Each stage is a window of time when specific, purposeful work happens.</p>
      <div class="s-pq-stages-grid">
        {stages.map(s => (
          <div class={`pq-stage pq-stage-${s.color}`}>
            <p class="pq-stage-label">
              <span class="pq-stage-badge">{s.num}</span>{s.stage}
            </p>
            <p class="pq-stage-time" set:html={s.timeframe} />
            <p class="pq-stage-body" set:html={s.body} />
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE WEEK 7 EVALUATION -->
  <section class="section pq-sec-white">
    <div class="container pq-narrow">
      <h2>The Week 7 evaluation</h2>
      <p>At around seven weeks, we conduct a structured behavioral evaluation of each puppy &mdash; a careful snapshot of how that puppy is behaving on that day.</p>
      <p>We&rsquo;re careful about what this evaluation is and isn&rsquo;t. It&rsquo;s an honest snapshot in time, not a prediction of the adult dog. Research consistently shows that puppy assessments don&rsquo;t predict adult temperament &mdash; because so much of who your dog becomes depends on what happens next, with you. That&rsquo;s the truth, and we&rsquo;d rather tell it to you than oversell a test.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WE MEASURE HOW IT TURNS OUT -->
  <section class="section pq-sec-cream">
    <div class="container pq-narrow">
      <h2>We measure how it turns out</h2>
      <p>Here&rsquo;s what sets PuppyQ apart: we don&rsquo;t stop at the day your puppy goes home. At eight months, we follow up with the full C-BARQ assessment to learn how our puppies are actually doing in their new lives.</p>
      <p>This gives us something rare &mdash; a real measure of outcomes, not just a record of the work we did. It lets us keep learning, keep improving, and keep raising better puppies with every litter.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT EVERY PUPPY GOES HOME WITH -->
  <section class="section s-pq-included">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What every puppy goes home with</h2>
      <p class="pq-included-intro">Every Adams Farm puppy comes home with three things:</p>
      <div class="s-pq-included-grid">
        {included.map(item => (
          <div class="pq-included-card">
            <h3 class="pq-included-title">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="pq-included-body" set:html={item.body} />
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CLOSING CTA -->
  <section class="s-pq-cta">
    <div class="container s-pq-cta-inner">
      <h2 class="s-pq-cta-heading">See our current puppies</h2>
      <a href="/puppies" class="btn btn-primary">See available puppies</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* ─── HERO ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pq-hero-body {
    color: rgba(237, 227, 208, 0.75);
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 20px 0 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.72;
  }

  /* ─── PROSE SECTIONS ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pq-sec-white { background: var(--color-white); }
  .pq-sec-cream { background: var(--color-cream-d); }
  .pq-narrow { max-width: 720px; }
  .pq-narrow h2 { color: var(--color-pine); margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .pq-narrow p {
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  .pq-narrow p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .pq-quote {
    margin: 8px 0 20px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-brass);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .pq-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-pine);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1.5px solid var(--color-brass);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
  }
  /* dark-background prose variant (light text on charcoal) */
  .pq-sec-dark {
    background: var(--color-charcoal-bg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-dark);
  }
  .pq-sec-dark .pq-narrow h2 { color: var(--color-card); }
  .pq-sec-dark .pq-narrow p { color: rgba(237, 227, 208, 0.8); }
  .pq-sec-dark .pq-quote { color: var(--color-card); }
  .pq-sec-dark .pq-link { color: var(--color-brass); }

  /* ─── FOUR STAGES ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .s-pq-stages {
    background: var(--color-charcoal-bg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-dark);
  }
  .s-pq-stages h2 { color: var(--color-card); margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .s-pq-stages-intro {
    color: rgba(237, 227, 208, 0.75);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.72;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 0 40px;
  }
  .s-pq-stages-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }
  .pq-stage {
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.07);
    padding: 28px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .pq-stage-green  { border-top: 4px solid var(--color-focus-green); }
  .pq-stage-blue   { border-top: 4px solid var(--color-calm-blue); }
  .pq-stage-yellow { border-top: 4px solid var(--color-excite-yellow); }
  .pq-stage-red    { border-top: 4px solid var(--color-feelings-red); }

  .pq-stage-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .pq-stage-green  .pq-stage-label { color: var(--color-focus-green); }
  .pq-stage-blue   .pq-stage-label { color: var(--color-calm-blue); }
  .pq-stage-yellow .pq-stage-label { color: #B8921E; }
  .pq-stage-red    .pq-stage-label { color: var(--color-feelings-red); }

  .pq-stage-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #fff;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .pq-stage-green  .pq-stage-badge { background: var(--color-focus-green); }
  .pq-stage-blue   .pq-stage-badge { background: var(--color-calm-blue); }
  .pq-stage-yellow .pq-stage-badge { background: var(--color-excite-yellow); color: var(--color-pine); }
  .pq-stage-red    .pq-stage-badge { background: var(--color-feelings-red); }

  .pq-stage-time {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-pine);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .pq-stage-body {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.72;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ─── WHAT EVERY PUPPY GOES HOME WITH ──────────────────────────── */
  .s-pq-included { background: var(--color-white); }
  .s-pq-included h2 { color: var(--color-pine); margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .pq-included-intro {
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }
  .s-pq-included-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }
  .pq-included-card {
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.07);
  }
  .pq-included-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-pine);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }
  .pq-included-body {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.72;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ─── CLOSING CTA ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .s-pq-cta {
    background: var(--color-charcoal-bg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-dark);
    padding: 72px 0;
  }
  .s-pq-cta-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    gap: 24px;
  }
  .s-pq-cta-heading { color: var(--color-card); margin: 0; }
  .s-pq-cta .btn-primary {
    background: var(--color-brass);
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    border-color: transparent;
  }
  .s-pq-cta .btn-primary:hover { filter: brightness(0.9); }

  /* ─── RESPONSIVE ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .s-pq-stages-grid   { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .s-pq-included-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .s-pq-stages-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
